Ian Ferguson of Evercore Partners Leaves to Join Bank of America

-- B y   L i a m   V a u g h a n
-- 
2011-10-11T08:45:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/ian-ferguson-of-evercore-partners-leaves-to-join-bank-of-america.html
Ian Ferguson, a senior managing
director at  Evercore Partners Inc. (EVR)  in London, has left the
independent advisory firm after three years to rejoin  Bank of
America Corp. (BAC) ’s Merrill Lynch.  Ferguson will join Bank of America, which acquired U.S.
investment bank Merrill Lynch in 2008, as a managing director in
U.K. investment banking at the beginning of next year,
spokeswoman Victoria Garrod said in a telephone interview. He
will report to Simon Mackenzie-Smith, chairman of U.K. corporate
and investment banking.  Ferguson left Merrill Lynch to join Evercore in September
2007. He was head of defense and aerospace at Merrill Lynch.  Evercore was founded in 1996 in New York by Roger Altman
former deputy U.S. Treasury Secretary. In August it acquired
London-based advisory firm Lexicon Partners Ltd. Andrew Sibbald,
chief executive officer of Evercore’s advisory unit in  Europe ,
declined to comment.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Liam Vaughan in London at 
